body:
This adds a way for the panel widget to be collapsed.

This feature was first skipped because of time constraint when releasing InstantSearch.js 3. This is a missing feature that was possible to implement in v2.

## Features

- Set the panel as "collapsible"
- Set the panel as "collapsible" with a collapsed state by default
- Drive the collapsed state with the helper state (fixes #2083)

## Usage

```js
search.addWidget(
  instantsearch.widgets.panel({
    collapsed: options => {
      return options && options.state && options.state.query.length === 0;
    },
    templates: {
      header: 'Collapsible panel',
      footer: 'Footer',
    },
  })(instantsearch.widgets.refinementList)({
    container,
    attribute: 'brand',
  })
);
```

## API

This introduces a new option in the `panel` widget called `collasped`.

`collasped`

> `SearchParameters => boolean` | no default

When this function is defined, it marks the panel as "collapsible". When the panel is collapsible, we add the CSS classes defined in the [Panel specs](https://instantsearch-css.netlify.com/widgets/panel/).

### Uncontrolled mode

To always collapse the panel:

```js
panel({
  // ...
  collapsed: () => false,
})
```

To collapse the panel until a query is typed:

```js
panel({
  collapsed: options => {
    return options && options.state && options.state.query.length === 0;
  },
});
```

### Controlled mode

Once the user starts interacting with the panel (with the ➕ and ➖ buttons), the panel enters in a controlled mode. It no longer reacts to the search parameters sent to the `collapsed` function.

